race.comment: MIDNIGHT MIRACLE (7) resumes for the Currie yard with 31% stable-striker KWT engaged. Raced well at the back of his last campaign and has trialled well at Warwick. Good enough and looks ready to go. QUARTER RED (4) did a good job to finish 2.6L from the winner 56 days ago at Gatton. He's been kept up to the mark with a trial placing at Toowoomba and jumps from a low barrier. Has more to offer for an in-form stable and this is a suitable assignment. REVITUP CHARLIE (8) has been within range in stronger provincial contests. He gets his chance in this company. BEACHSIDE BABE (5) got caught wide at the Sunshine Coast but was beaten less than 2L at the Gold Coast prior. That would have her in the finish.
